<head>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bootstrap/5.1.3/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bootstrap/5.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css"
  />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/main.css" />
</head>

<div class="container py-5">
  <h1 class="text-center display-4 faq-title">FAQs - NotesMakr</h1>
  <p class="text-center fs-5">
    Your ultimate guide to storing your "dumbass thoughts" with style!
  </p>

  <div class="row justify-content-center mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-8">
      <div class="question">Q: So, what exactly does NotesMakr do?</div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: Oh, only the most important thing ever: it gives you a place to jot
          down your random thoughts, rants, epiphanies, and maybe a few grocery
          lists! Think of it as a journal for all the stuff that pops into your
          head when you’re supposed to be focusing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">Q: How do I add a note here? Is it magic?</div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: Almost! Just hit that <strong>“Add Note”</strong> button and let
          your thumbs do the talking. Type in your note, hit save, and voila!
          Your thoughts, safely tucked away like a squirrel's nuts for winter.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">
        Q: Can I update my notes? What if I type like a boomer?
      </div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: No sweat! Just click on your note, choose <strong>“Edit”</strong>,
          and fix all those typos (or add more if that’s your thing). Once
          you’re done, save the changes, and your note is back on track!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">
        Q: What if I wanna delete a note? Like, gone gone?
      </div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: When a note has overstayed its welcome, hit the
          <strong>“Delete”</strong> button, and poof—it's history. No trace left
          behind. Just be sure you mean it, 'cause there’s no going back!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">
        Q: Can I store unlimited thoughts, or is there a catch?
      </div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: The sky’s the limit, friend! Add as many “dumbass thoughts” as your
          heart desires. We don’t judge, and we certainly don’t limit genius.
          Just keep 'em coming!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">Q: Can I access NotesMakr on my phone?</div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: Duh! Whip out that phone anytime, anywhere, and NotesMakr’s ready
          to capture your brilliance (or nonsense). We’re mobile-friendly for
          all your on-the-go brain dumps!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">Q: Any tips for organizing all this chaos?</div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: We recommend tagging your notes or grouping similar thoughts
          together. You’ll thank yourself later when you’re trying to find that
          one genius idea at 2 a.m.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">
        Q: What if I forget to save a note? Does it auto-save?
      </div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: We’d love to say yes, but we aren’t mind readers... yet! For now,
          just make sure you hit that save button. Trust us, your brain dump
          deserves it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">
        Q: Is NotesMakr secure? Like, my notes aren’t gonna leak, right?
      </div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: Your secrets are safe with us. NotesMakr uses top-notch security to
          keep your random musings safe from prying eyes. We got you!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="question">Q: What’s the best way to use NotesMakr?</div>
      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: However you want! Whether it's capturing shower thoughts,
          late-night rants, or brilliant epiphanies, NotesMakr is your loyal,
          no-judgment buddy. Let it all out!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="questionbox flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900"
      >
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
          <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto my-10 bg-white p-5 rounded-md shadow-md">
            <div class="text-center">
              <h1
                class="my-3 text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200"
              >
                Contact Us
              </h1>
              <p class="text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-400">
                Fill up the form below to send us a message.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-7">
              <form
                action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit"
                method="POST"
                id="form"
                class="space-y-6"
              >
                <input
                  type="hidden"
                  name="access_key"
                  value="<%= accessKey %>"
                />
                <input
                  type="hidden"
                  name="subject"
                  value="New Submission from Web3Forms"
                />
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  name="botcheck"
                  id=""
                  style="display: none"
                />

                <!-- First and Last Name -->
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-2">
                  <div>
                    <label
                      for="fname"
                      class="block mb-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
                      >Name</label
                    >
                    <input
                      type="text"
                      name="name"
                      id="first_name"
                      placeholder="Your Name"
                      required
                      class="form-control"
                    />
                  </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Email and Phone -->
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-2">
                  <div>
                    <label
                      for="email"
                      class="block mb-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
                      >Email Address</label
                    >
                    <input
                      type="email"
                      name="email"
                      id="email"
                      placeholder="Your Email"
                      required
                      class="form-control"
                    />
                  </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Message -->
                <div class="mb-3">
                  <label
                    for="message"
                    class="block mb-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
                    >Your Message</label
                  >
                  <textarea
                    rows="5"
                    name="message"
                    id="message"
                    placeholder="Your Message"
                    required
                    class="form-control"
                  ></textarea>
                </div>

                <!-- Submit Button -->
                <div>
                  <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">
                    Send Message
                  </button>
                </div>
              </form>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center mt-5">
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Go Back Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  const form = document.getElementById("form");
  const result = document.getElementById("result");

  form.addEventListener("submit", function (e) {
    const formData = new FormData(form);
    e.preventDefault();
    var object = {};
    formData.forEach((value, key) => {
      object[key] = value;
    });
    var json = JSON.stringify(object);
    result.innerHTML = "Please wait...";

    fetch("https://api.web3forms.com/submit", {
      method: "POST",
      headers: {
        "Content-Type": "application/json",
        Accept: "application/json",
      },
      body: json,
    })
      .then(async (response) => {
        let json = await response.json();
        if (response.status == 200) {
          result.innerHTML = json.message;
          result.classList.remove("text-gray-500");
          result.classList.add("text-green-500");
        } else {
          console.log(response);
          result.innerHTML = json.message;
          result.classList.remove("text-gray-500");
          result.classList.add("text-red-500");
        }
      })
      .catch((error) => {
        console.log(error);
        result.innerHTML = "Something went wrong!";
      })
      .then(function () {
        form.reset();
        setTimeout(() => {
          result.style.display = "none";
        }, 5000);
      });
  });
</script>
